metadata.name: Ilıca falls in winter
metadata.description:
It is located within Pınarbaşı’s Ilıca Village, has 12 km. distance from 
the province. From Ilıca Village, the pathway takes about half an hour.
The water falls from about 10 km. height and a pool generated 
from the falling point of the stream. The most important aspect of this 
fall is that the natural pool is surrounded by numerous trees and plants. 
Again if the road from the top parts of the fall was taken, the concavities 
and carvings of the water generated on the rocks throughout the years 
has given the city a different beauty.
